{
  "name": "glassbright",
  "description": "Crystal singing bowls catching the sun, ringing pure and clear over still water. Frictionless glassy sine-pure tones with a faint inharmonic glassy shimmer that decays fast — ethereal yet wide-awake and joyful, never icy. A rounded glass-bottle bass grounds without weight; a rubbed crystal-bowl lead swells in and sings the melody while a higher struck-glass rim answers; a warm wineglass hum fills the middle; a fingertip-on-rim ping and tiny high droplets scatter light; a slow bowed-glass bloom and a shimmering three-tone ripple glow like sunlight on water; a faint glassy breath sits just before a bowl sings, and a bright sun-glint flicks at the top. A major pentatonic @ A=432, hall reverb, additive and clean. Long bell rings, no buzz, all light — every register covered, never dreary.",
